        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The audible warning alarm can be temporarily disabled while performing service in the cab.</para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury, park the vehicle on a flat level surface and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate both the Select/Reset switch on the bottom right side of the instrument cluster
                    and the panel dimmer rocker switch on the left lower instrument panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the ignition in the on position and alarm sounding, simultaneously depress the
                    panel dimmer switch (either up or down) and the Select/Reset switch.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The alarm will be silenced in approximately 3 to 5 seconds.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The alarm will return to normal operation after the ignition key is cycled or the engine
                    speed exceeds 325 rpm.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
